<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06240087 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06240087 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  JUVENILE; AUTO; DEATH; INJURY; ACCIDENT; ALCOHOL; ABUSE; CRIME  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Three San Jose teens -- two of them sisters -- were killed and a fourthcritically injured early today when a man suspected of drunken driving drovethrough a stop sign and crashed into their small pickup truck.;   San Josepolice today booked Robert Lee Buhler, 24, of San Jose into Santa Clara CountyJail on suspicion of homicide and felony drunken driving.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  3 S.J. TEENS KILLED IN SUSPECTED DUI CRASH  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The four youths had just made a midnight run to a nearby grocery for snacksand were returning home when the accident happened at Alma and Vine streets,about a block from the teen-agers' homes, at 12:04 a.m.;   &quot;I don't think theyknew what hit them,&quot; traffic investigator Greg Wagstaff said, adding, &quot;Therewas no fault on the part of the teen-agers except being at the wrong place atthe wrong time.&quot;;   Dead were Salvador Castro, the 18-year-old driver, andMarisol Perez, 17, and her 15-year-old sister Rocio. A 13-year-old girlsuffered critical injuries.;   Two passengers in Buhler's pickup, where policefound unopened bottles of beer and whiskey, also were hurt, suffering minor tomoderate injuries.;   Marisol Perez was thrown from the bed of the pickuptruck as the suspect's pickup pushed the smaller vehicle 85 feet through theintersection.;   She ended up under the wreckage and died in the emergencyroom at San Jose Medical Center at 12:46 a.m.;   Rocio Perez was found bypolice in the bed of the truck and pronounced dead at the scene.;   Buhler,who allegedly had been driving south on Vine Street for several blocks at morethan 65 miles an hour, was treated at Valley Medical Center before beingbooked.;   &quot;He had an odor of alcohol,&quot; Wagstaff said, adding that Buhler hada valid driver's license but had several prior arrests for driving on asuspended license. And three years ago he had a prior drunken drivingoffense.;   Buhler's passengers -- Gary Wright, 26, of San Jose and JohnRynhard, 33, of Campbell -- were treated at Valley Medical Center and released.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  BETTY BARNACLE, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910827  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  336  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday, August 27, 199100240087,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENGFRONT  </LANGUAGE></DOC>